Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @Potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @Oil{to taste}, season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Beat @Egg{1} (double for 4p) in a #bowl{} with a pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}.

To another bowl, add @Breadcrumbs{1%pack} and @Paprika{1%sachet}. Season with salt and pepper and mix.

Toss @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%g} first in egg, then in breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands after handling chicken and its packaging. Discard any remaining egg.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing used to keep it fresh.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with enough @Oil{to taste} to coat the bottom.

Once hot, fry the chicken until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a #plate{} lined with kitchen paper.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Make sure the oil is hot so the chicken fries properly!

Meanwhile, chop the @Tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

In a bowl for the salad, toss the chopped tomato and pepper together with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}. Season to taste with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

When 3 mins of cooking time remain for the chips, remove from the oven and scatter over the @Grated Cheese{50%g}.

Cook until melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the cheesy chips and crunchy chicken between plates.

Serve with the refreshing salsa.

Add @Ketchup{2%sachets} on the side for dipping.